==English==
===Noun===
'''focus''' (''plural'' '''[[foci]]''' ''or'' '''[[focuses]]''')

# (''optics'') A point at which reflected or refracted rays of light converge.
#: ''The heat of sunlight at the focus of a magnifying glass can easily set dry leaves on fire.''
# (''mathematics'') A point at which rays reflected from a curve or surface converge.
# (''photography, cinematography; uncountable'') The [[focal plane]].
#: ''Unfortunately, the license plate is out of focus in this image.''
# (''photography, cinematography; uncountable'') Definition or clarity due to proximity to the [[focal plane]].  <!-- urgh -->
#: ''During this scene, the boy's face shifts subtly from soft focus into sharp focus.''
# (''uncountable'') Concentration of attention.
#: ''I believe I can bring the high degree of focus required for this important job.''

